### What I have been upto:

So far in this module, I have learnt various things on Git. The latest block which I studied covered how we collaborate in teams using git enabled platforms such as Github. I went through the tutorial and practiced it later. You can find my work here: [My first hello-world project](https://github.com/anandsesha/hello-world.git) and some additional practice of the same concepts here : [A practice project](https://github.com/anandsesha/remote-branching-practice.git)

The commands I came across while studing this tutorial are:
 
```markdown

1. `git remote add origin https://github.com/anandsesha/hello-world.git`

2. `git remote -v`
 
3. `git push origin master`

4. `git log --oneline --decorate --graph --all`

5. `git checkout master`

6. `git clone https://github.com/anandsesha/hello-world.git`

7. `git checkout -b "xyz"`

8. `git commit -am ""`

9. `git push origin xyz`

10. `git fetch origin`

11. `git merge origin/master`

12. `git pull origin/master`

```
In addition to this, on Github I have learnt how to **create and close issues** and about **pull and merge requests**.

Looking forward to learning more!!
